---
import LessonLayout from '../../layouts/LessonLayout.astro';
---
<LessonLayout
  title="Demo Day"
  track="young-builders"
  week={12}
  phase="Phase 4: Capstone"
  duration="60 min"
  emoji="🚀"
  objective="Present your capstone project and reflect on the full journey"
>
  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-builder-700 mb-3">🎯 Learning Objective</h2>
    <p class="bg-builder-50 border-l-4 border-builder-400 p-4 rounded-r-xl text-gray-700">
      You will present your project to an audience, explain your technical choices, reflect on 12 weeks of learning, and set goals for what comes next.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">🛠️ Materials</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Your completed project code</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ An audience (family, friends — even online!)</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ A "slide deck" or poster (optional but impressive!)</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Your notebook from all 12 weeks</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">📋 Activity Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Demo Prep (15 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Practice your 5-minute demo. Structure: (1) What problem does it solve? (2) How does it work? (3) Live demo. (4) What you'd improve. Run through it once alone.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Live Demo (20 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Present to your audience! Answer questions. If something breaks — debug it live, explaining what you're doing. That IS the skill!</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Journey Review (15 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Flip through your notebook. For each phase, share: what was the hardest concept? What clicked? What are you most proud of?</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-builder-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">4</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">What's Next? (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Write 3 goals for the next 12 weeks. What will you learn? What will you build? Set the next challenge.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💻 Demo Script Helper</h2>
    <pre is:raw class="bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-5 overflow-x-auto text-sm leading-relaxed"><code># demo_day.py — Week 12: Young Builders
# Run this before your demo to make sure everything works!
import time

class ReachyMock:
    def say(self, msg): print(f"🔊 {msg}"); time.sleep(0.5)
    def wave(self): print("👋 *waves*"); time.sleep(0.5)
    def set_emotion(self, e): print(f"😊 *{e}*"); time.sleep(0.3)
    def go_to_rest(self): print("😌 *rest*"); time.sleep(0.5)

try:
    from reachy_mini import ReachyMini
    robot = ReachyMini()
    print("✅ Hardware ready!")
except Exception:
    robot = ReachyMock()
    print("🎮 Simulator ready!")

# Pre-demo system check
print("\n🔍 Running system check...")
checks = ["Connection", "Movement", "Voice", "Project code"]
for check in checks:
    time.sleep(0.3)
    print(f"  ✅ {check}: OK")

print("\n🚀 All systems go! Time to demo!\n")

# Intro sequence
robot.set_emotion("happy")
robot.wave()
robot.say("Hello everyone! I'm Reachy.")
robot.say("Today I'm going to show you what I built with my Young Builder!")
time.sleep(1)
robot.say("Here we go!")

# YOUR PROJECT RUNS HERE
# (run your actual project code)
print("\n[YOUR PROJECT CODE HERE]\n")

# Outro
robot.say("That was my project! Thank you for watching!")
robot.say("I'm a Young Builder, and I built this with Python!")
robot.wave()

print("\n🏆 Demo complete! You're officially a Young Builder!")</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8 bg-indigo-50 border-2 border-indigo-300 rounded-2xl p-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-indigo-700 mb-3">🏆 Young Builder Certificate</h2>
    <div class="border-4 border-indigo-400 rounded-xl p-6 text-center bg-white">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🤖⭐🚀</div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-extrabold mb-2">Certificate of Excellence</h3>
      <p class="text-lg mb-2">This certifies that</p>
      <div class="border-b-2 border-gray-400 w-48 mx-auto mb-2 h-8"></div>
      <p class="text-lg mb-4">has successfully completed the</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-builder-600 mb-2">Young Builders 12-Week Robotics Curriculum</p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">demonstrating mastery of computational thinking, Python programming, and AI concepts with Reachy Mini</p>
      <div class="text-3xl mt-4">🔧 💻 🤖</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">🗺️ What's Next?</h2>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Go Deeper in Python</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Classes, modules, file I/O, APIs. Python is used everywhere!</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Explore ML/AI</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Train your own model with scikit-learn or TensorFlow Lite.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Hardware Hacking</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Try Arduino, Raspberry Pi, or build your own robot from parts!</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💬 Reflection Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-blue-800">💭 What concept from these 12 weeks will you use in the real world?</p></div>
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-blue-800">💭 What was the moment you felt most like a "real programmer"?</p></div>
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-blue-800">💭 What advice would you give to someone just starting Week 1?</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">👪 Parent Tips</h2>
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-xl p-5 text-gray-700">
      <p>💡 Your child just completed a structured 12-week engineering curriculum covering algorithms, debugging, sensors, vision, voice interfaces, and a full project. That is genuinely impressive.</p>
      <p class="mt-2">💡 The best next step: let THEM choose. Follow their curiosity — not a curriculum.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LessonLayout>
